Net::Braintree

Braintree considers this library to be deprecated; current integrations
are supported, but no new feature development is planned at this time. For
more details visit the following URL:

https://support.braintreepayments.com/customer/portal/articles/1763061-status-of-the-perl-client-library

Some active users of this module are maintaining this fork focused on
stability and minimal changes needed for bug fixes and missing features:

https://github.com/interchange/braintree_perl

Another community fork has renamed and greatly remodeled the module:

https://metacpan.org/pod/WebService::Braintree

INSTALLATION

To install this module, run the following commands:

	perl Makefile.PL
	make
	make test
	make install

SUPPORT AND DOCUMENTATION

After installing, you can find documentation for this module with the
perldoc command.

    perldoc Net::Braintree

You can also look for information at:

    GitHub fork maintaining Net::Braintree
        https://github.com/interchange/braintree_perl

    RT, CPAN's request tracker (Braintree has ignored bug reports here)
        https://rt.cpan.org/Public/Dist/Display.html?Name=Net-Braintree

    AnnoCPAN, Annotated CPAN documentation
        http://annocpan.org/dist/Net-Braintree

    CPAN Ratings
        http://cpanratings.perl.org/d/Net-Braintree

    MetaCPAN
        https://metacpan.org/pod/Net::Braintree

OPEN SOURCE ATTRIBUTION

A list of open source projects that help power Braintree can be found at
https://www.braintreepayments.com/developers/open-source

